@page "/"
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]

<PageMeta Title="ScamAlert — watch over the PCs of people you care for"
          Description="Sign up, install on their Windows PC, and get SMS when someone tries to connect remotely. $7.99/month."
          CanonicalPath="/" />

<section class="hero-sa mb-5">
    <div class="row g-4 align-items-center">
        <div class="col-lg-7">
            <p class="text-uppercase small fw-semibold text-sa-accent mb-2">Stop remote-access scams</p>
            <h1 class="display-6 fw-semibold mb-3">You cannot sit at every keyboard. ScamAlert texts <em>you</em> when someone reaches theirs.</h1>
            <p class="lead text-secondary">
                Sign up, install protection on the Windows PC of someone you care for, and put <strong>your number</strong> on the alert list.
                When a scammer or fake “tech support” tries to control their computer remotely, <strong>you find out</strong>—they do not have to watch for alerts or learn technical tools.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-3"><span class="badge rounded-pill badge-sa">$7.99/month · one account, you manage it</span></p>
            <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-2">
                <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/signup">Protect someone I care for</a>
                <a class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-lg" href="/pricing">See pricing</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-5">
            <div class="card border-0 hero-card">
                <div class="card-body p-4">
                    <h2 class="h5 mb-3">You handle it—they do not have to</h2>
                    <ul class="mb-0 text-secondary sa-checklist">
                        <li>Install on <em>their</em> PC; alerts go to <em>your</em> phone</li>
                        <li>Watches for signs someone is trying to connect to their PC remotely</li>
                        <li>Built for refund scams and fake “let me fix your computer” calls</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="mb-5">
    <h2 class="h4 mb-4 text-center">Who you are protecting</h2>
    <div class="row g-3">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h3 class="h6 text-sa-accent">Older loved ones</h3>
                    <p class="small text-secondary mb-0">They may not spot a scammer on the phone asking them to install remote software. You still get notified when access is attempted.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h3 class="h6 text-sa-accent">Long-distance family</h3>
                    <p class="small text-secondary mb-0">When you cannot drop by in person, your phone gets the alert the moment something looks wrong on their PC—not after the fact.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h3 class="h6 text-sa-accent">Anyone who might trust a caller</h3>
                    <p class="small text-secondary mb-0">Scammers sound convincing. Even careful people get talked into letting someone onto their PC. ScamAlert gives you a heads-up to call them first.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="mb-5 py-4 px-3 rounded sa-muted-panel">
    <h2 class="h4 mb-4">How it works</h2>
    <div class="row g-4">
        <div class="col-md-4 text-center">
            <div class="step-num">1</div>
            <h3 class="h6">You sign up</h3>
            <p class="small text-secondary">Create the account and add your mobile for alerts.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4 text-center">
            <div class="step-num">2</div>
            <h3 class="h6">Install on their PC</h3>
            <p class="small text-secondary">Visit them, run the installer, pair with a code from your dashboard.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4 text-center">
            <div class="step-num">3</div>
            <h3 class="h6">You get the text</h3>
            <p class="small text-secondary">Suspicious remote access hits your phone—call them, confirm, and help shut it down.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-center mb-0 mt-3">
        <a href="/how-it-works">Full walkthrough</a> · <a href="/pricing">$7.99/month</a>
    </p>
</section>

<section class="text-center mb-4">
    <h2 class="h4 mb-2">Peace of mind when you cannot be in the room</h2>
    <p class="text-secondary col-lg-8 mx-auto">
        ScamAlert does not replace talking with people you care about regarding scams—it adds a safety net when criminals push remote access anyway.
    </p>
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/signup">Sign up to protect them</a>
</section>
